rest_of_day_open: I see it going about the way things have been recently. I'm working on making videos to replace normally teaching after school lessons and I expect to make slow progress on them. The quarantine situation has made me anxious and I'm sure I'll still be dealing with that. Still spending time with family while I'm stuck here staying with them.
critical_positive: We were able to quickly find something we have in common, which was our mutual love of cats. I think even without that, the current situation provided some common ground to start from and we did start there, but the conversation really felt like it clicked once we got to something else we both liked and could talk about outside of that.
critical_negative: We both had moments of struggling to continue finding topics, though that didn't tend to drag on for long. Trying to talk continuously for a set amount of time provides a challenge and I feel like neither of us were really used to having extended conversations with a stranger. I think we were both enjoying it, just there were some lulls in the flow that we weren't sure what to do with.

rest_of_day_open: I see it going pretty well. I have a bunch of homework to complete, and a couple of essays to turn in, so it will be busy for sure. There will be time at the end of the weeks for me to give away some kittens that were born in my backyard.
critical_positive: We were both willing to be there and complete the requirements in this task. We were both friendly/slightly awkward people, so there wasn't too much discomfort when we did have quiet pauses for a moment. We were both willing to listen to what each other had to say as well.
critical_negative: It was hard to figure out what to talk about, and when we did latch onto a topic, it wasn't the easiest to switch from that one, or to come up with a new topic once that one ran dry. I don't have too many complaints about the quality of our conversation.
